{"query": "WITH sal_hist AS (
    SELECT
        s.employee_id,
        s.from_date,
        s.to_date,
        s.amount,
        LAG(s.amount) OVER (PARTITION BY s.employee_id ORDER BY s.from_date) AS prev_amount
    FROM employees.salary AS s
),
chgs AS (
    SELECT
        employee_id,
        from_date,
        to_date,
        amount,
        prev_amount,
        CASE WHEN prev_amount IS NULL THEN NULL ELSE amount - prev_amount END AS delta_amt,
        CASE WHEN prev_amount IS NULL OR prev_amount = 0 THEN NULL
             ELSE CAST((amount - prev_amount) * 100.0 / prev_amount AS DECIMAL(10,2)) END AS delta_pct
    FROM sal_hist
),
dept_hist AS (
    SELECT
        de.employee_id,
        de.from_date,
        de.to_date,
        d.dept_name
    FROM employees.department_employee AS de
    JOIN employees.department AS d
      ON d.id = de.department_id
),
title_hist AS (
    SELECT
        t.employee_id,
        t.from_date,
        COALESCE(t.to_date, CONVERT(date,'9999-12-31')) AS to_date,
        t.title
    FROM employees.title AS t
)
SELECT
    'salary' AS kind,
    c.employee_id,
    c.from_date,
    c.to_date,
    CAST(c.amount AS nvarchar(50)) AS value,
    CAST(c.delta_amt AS nvarchar(50)) AS delta_amt,
    CAST(c.delta_pct AS nvarchar(50)) AS delta_pct
FROM chgs AS c

UNION ALL

SELECT
    'department' AS kind,
    d.employee_id,
    d.from_date,
    d.to_date,
    d.dept_name AS value,
    NULL AS delta_amt,
    NULL AS delta_pct
FROM dept_hist AS d

UNION ALL

SELECT
    'title' AS kind,
    th.employee_id,
    th.from_date,
    th.to_date,
    th.title AS value,
    NULL AS delta_amt,
    NULL AS delta_pct
FROM title_hist AS th
ORDER BY from_date, kind;"}

{"data_analysis_python_code": "import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

path = '/home/daytona/474eca9b-2168-48be-a4cd-a086f2f77756.json'
df = pd.read_json(path)

# Parse dates
for c in ['from_date','to_date']:
    df[c] = pd.to_datetime(df[c])

# Separate
sal = df[df['kind']=='salary'].copy()
# salary values
sal['amount'] = pd.to_numeric(sal['value'], errors='coerce')
sal['delta_amt'] = pd.to_numeric(sal['delta_amt'], errors='coerce')
sal['delta_pct'] = pd.to_numeric(sal['delta_pct'], errors='coerce')

# Compute summary stats
first_row = sal.sort_values('from_date').iloc[0]
last_row = sal.sort_values('from_date').iloc[-1]
summary = {
    'first_effective_date': first_row['from_date'].date().isoformat(),
    'first_salary': int(first_row['amount']),
    'last_effective_date': last_row['from_date'].date().isoformat(),
    'current_salary': int(last_row['amount']),
    'total_change_amt': int(last_row['amount'] - first_row['amount']),
    'total_change_pct': float((last_row['amount'] - first_row['amount']) / first_row['amount'] * 100.0),
    'num_changes': int(len(sal)-1),
    'num_raises': int((sal['delta_amt']>0).sum()),
    'num_cuts': int((sal['delta_amt']<0).sum()),
    'largest_raise_amt': int(sal['delta_amt'].max()),
    'largest_raise_pct': float(sal.loc[sal['delta_amt'].idxmax(), 'delta_pct']) if sal['delta_amt'].notna().any() else np.nan,
    'largest_cut_amt': int(sal['delta_amt'].min()),
    'largest_cut_pct': float(sal.loc[sal['delta_amt'].idxmin(), 'delta_pct']) if (sal['delta_amt']<0).any() else np.nan,
}

# Department and title intervals
dept = df[df['kind']=='department'].copy().sort_values('from_date')
titles = df[df['kind']=='title'].copy().sort_values('from_date')

# Build a title timeline mapped onto salary effective dates (as-of join)
sal_dates = sal[['from_date']].sort_values('from_date').copy()
# For each salary date, find latest title starting <= date

titles_sorted = titles.sort_values('from_date')

def asof_value(date, hist):
    sub = hist[hist['from_date']<=date]
    if sub.empty:
        return None
    return sub.iloc[-1]['value']

sal_dates['title_at_change'] = sal_dates['from_date'].apply(lambda d: asof_value(d, titles_sorted))

# Visualizations
sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid')

# 1) Salary over time
plt.figure(figsize=(10,4))
ax = sns.lineplot(data=sal.sort_values('from_date'), x='from_date', y='amount', marker='o', linewidth=2)
ax.set(title='Salary history (effective date)', xlabel='Effective date', ylabel='Salary amount')
# annotate title changes roughly (vertical lines)
for _, r in titles_sorted.iterrows():
    ax.axvline(r['from_date'], color='gray', linestyle='--', alpha=0.25)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# 2) Salary change distribution
chg = sal[sal['delta_amt'].notna()].copy()
plt.figure(figsize=(8,3.5))
ax = sns.histplot(chg['delta_pct'], bins=10, kde=True, color=sns.color_palette()[0])
ax.set(title='Distribution of salary change % per adjustment', xlabel='Change (%)', ylabel='Count')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# 3) Table-like view: salary changes with title at the time
out = sal.sort_values('from_date')[['from_date','to_date','amount','delta_amt','delta_pct']].copy()
out['title_at_change'] = sal_dates['title_at_change'].values

print('SALARY_SUMMARY')
print(summary)
print('\nDEPARTMENT_HISTORY')
print(dept[['from_date','to_date','value']].rename(columns={'value':'department'}).to_string(index=False))
print('\nTITLE_HISTORY')
print(titles[['from_date','to_date','value']].rename(columns={'value':'title'}).to_string(index=False))
print('\nSALARY_CHANGE_TABLE (first 25 rows)')
print(out.head(25).to_string(index=False))
"}
